@startuml
title PQR Hybrid Lakehouse - Flujo de Datos ETL (Raw -> Bronze -> Silver -> Gold)
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle
left to right direction

actor "Simulador / Fuente" as Source
component "apps/simulator/\ngenerate_pqrs_data.py" as Sim

database "RustFS S3\nbucket raw/" as Raw
component "Pipeline 1\nraw_to_bronze.py\nnormalize_event()" as P1
database "Postgres bronze.pqrs_events" as Bronze

component "Pipeline 2\nbronze_to_silver.py\nbuild_ticket_record()" as P2
database "Postgres silver.tickets\nsilver.messages\nsilver.status_events\nsilver.attachments?" as Silver

component "Pipeline 3\ngold_to_postgres.py\nbuild_upsert_statement()" as P3
database "Postgres gold.kpi_*\n(kpi_volume_daily,\nkpi_backlog_daily,\nkpi_sla_daily...)" as Gold

database "Postgres meta.etl_runs\nmeta.data_quality" as Meta
component "Prefect Flow" as Flow
component "Dask Cluster" as Dask

Source --> Sim : genera eventos
Sim --> Raw : escribe JSONL/Parquet raw

Flow --> Dask : ejecuta tasks distribuidas
Dask --> P1
Dask --> P2
Dask --> P3

P1 --> Raw : lee raw objects
P1 --> Bronze : carga eventos normalizados
P1 --> Meta : registra run + conteos

P2 --> Bronze : lee eventos
P2 --> Silver : curacion/enriquecimiento
P2 --> Meta : validaciones calidad

P3 --> Silver : agrega medidas
P3 --> Gold : upsert KPIs
P3 --> Meta : estado final del run

note bottom
Capas:
Raw = objeto inmutable de entrada
Bronze = eventos normalizados
Silver = entidades curadas y trazables
Gold = metricas agregadas para BI/dashboard
end note

@enduml
